name: chinese zodiac sign postcards series 1
description:
We already have listed the zodiac sign tees:http://pinkfrognyc.com/category/fashionfrog-ny-tee?page=2
now the postcards are here!

12 animals (in order: rat, ox, tiger, rabbit, dragon, snake, horse, sheep or goat, monkey, rooster, dog, and boar or pig) represent the rotating 12-year cycle that is the basis of the Chinese Zodiac. 

Years Corresponding to RAT:
1900 1912 1924 1936 1948 1960 1972 1984 1996 2008 2020

Years Corresponding to OX:
1901 1913 1925 1937 1949 1961 1973 1985 1997 2009 2021

Years Corresponding to TIGER:
1902 1914 1926 1938 1950 1962 1974 1986 1998 2010 2022

Years Corresponding to RABBIT:
1903 1915 1927 1939 1951 1963 1975 1987 1999 2011 2023

Years Corresponding to DRAGON:
1904 1916 1928 1940 1952 1964 1976 1988 2000 2012 2024

Years Corresponding to SNAKE:
1905 1917 1929 1941 1953 1965 1977 1989 2001 2013 2025

Years Corresponding to HORSE:
1906 1918 1930 1942 1954 1966 1978 1990 2002 2014 2026

Years Corresponding to SHEEP:
1907 1919 1931 1943 1955 1967 1979 1991 2003 2015 2027

Years Corresponding to MONKEY:
1908 1920 1932 1944 1956 1968 1980 1992 2004 2016 2028

Years Corresponding to ROOSTER:
1909 1921 1933 1945 1957 1969 1981 1993 2005 2017 2029

Years Corresponding to DOG:
1910 1922 1934 1946 1958 1970 1982 1994 2006 2018 2030

Years Corresponding to BOAR:
1911 1923 1935 1947 1959 1971 1983 1995 2007 2019 2031

Each postcard measures 4x6 and is high quality printed on premium 190 GSM archival acid-free 100% cotton card wrapped in a beautiful, intimate and handmade feel. The frames in photo are for illustrative purposes only. These postcards look fantastic framed and hanging together as a set.

Please indicate which 4 postcards you choose if you pick 4 cards as an order. 

Please contact us for international shipping or if you are located at Hawaii/Alaska.

name: framed print of Chinese Painting on canvas - Camellia and Terpsiphone Paradisi
description:
Camellia & Terpsiphone Paradisi
sku #: framecp1

This piece is a gongbi watercolor painting that is painted on rice paper, and printed on canvas. Prints on canvas create a new fresh perspective on traditional Chinese Painting, it adds a new element to Chinese Painting. It has been selected for galleries' exhibitions in NYC.

Our original Chinese Watercolor Paintings are painted with brushes on rice paper or silk integrated with traditional Chinese Painting skills in two different styles: ''(gong bi) and ''(xie yi).

Gongbi () Paintings, literally "detailed strokes", are paintings characterized by fine brushwork. Gongbi is a technique in Chinese painting. The name is from the Chinese Gong chin meaning tidy (meticulous brush technique). The technique uses highly detailed brushstrokes that delimits details very precisely and without independent or expressive variation.

Printed with pro printer and matted in white. Framed in a 8x10/11x14 in clean cut black wood frame. Each print is signed by the artist.

name: framed print of Chinese Painting on canvas - Untitled
description:
Untitled
sku #: framecp5

This piece is a xieyi ink painting that is painted on rice paper, and printed on canvas. Prints on canvas create a new fresh perspective on traditional Chinese Painting, it adds a new element to Chinese Painting. It has been selected for galleries' exhibitions in NYC.

Our original Chinese Watercolor Paintings are painted with brushes on rice paper or silk integrated with traditional Chinese Painting skills in two different styles: ''(gong bi) and ''(xie yi).

Xieyi () style Chinese painting uses broad, expressionistic strokes of ink applied to paper, typically raw rice paper. This style is also referred to as "freehand" Chinese painting. Xieyi literally means "writing the meaning down" and the artists were typically scholars. Paintings are created in a single sitting and the artist is focused on expressing the Qi or vital spirit of the painting. The paper represents yin and the brushstrokes yang for the artist. Landscapes, human figures and flora and fauna are typical subjects of Xieyi painting.

Printed with pro printer and matted in white. Framed in a 8x10/11x14 in clean cut black wood frame. Each print is signed by the artist.
